# Architecture Map
#
# Two sections in one file:
#   1. CONCEPTS: concept -> entry-point file -> ADR -> how-to-extend
#   2. ADR CATALOG: ADR-NNN -> topic -> title (overview of all decisions)
#
# Single-call lookup: `grep "ADR-79" src/ARCHITECTURE.map` returns
# both the concept rows that reference ADR-79 AND the catalog row
# with its title. `grep "<concept>" src/ARCHITECTURE.map` finds the
# entry-point file and the relevant ADR number.
#
# Status, phase, last-change live in the backlog row, not here.
# Run `grep "ADR-NNN" _devprocess/context/10_backlog.md` for status.
#
# Format Section 1: `concept | entry-point | adr | how-to-extend`
# Format Section 2: `ADR-NNN | topic | title`
# Columns are separated by ` | `. Lines starting with `#` are comments.

# =====================================================================
# SECTION 1: CONCEPTS
